01:01:01.524 --> 01:01:03.559 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, before we conclude, 

01:01:03.559 --> 01:01:06.896 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’d like to visit the city of Cuzco in Peru, 

01:01:06.896 --> 01:01:11.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
where we have 
a Remote Translation Office, or RTO.

01:01:11.934 --> 01:01:15.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
The city of Cuzco is a stopover 
for travelers to Machu Picchu, 

01:01:16.839 --> 01:01:20.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
a historic sanctuary 
of the former Inca Empire, 

01:01:20.977 --> 01:01:23.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
located high up in the mountains. 

01:01:23.479 --> 01:01:27.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
Machu Picchu is an architectural marvel. 

01:01:27.316 --> 01:01:30.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
The design is earthquake resistant. 

01:01:30.486 --> 01:01:33.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
Giant stones were cut so precisely 

01:01:33.423 --> 01:01:36.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
that in many places a piece of paper 

01:01:36.626 --> 01:01:39.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
cannot fit in between them. 

01:01:39.128 --> 01:01:42.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
At such high altitudes, 
you can also see llamas, 

01:01:42.632 --> 01:01:45.935 line:90% position:50% align:center
which are raised 
in the Andes Mountains. 

01:01:45.935 --> 01:01:48.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Inca people spoke Quechua, 

01:01:48.171 --> 01:01:50.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
a language that is spoken 

01:01:50.173 --> 01:01:53.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
by millions of Peruvians today.

01:01:53.109 --> 01:01:56.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
There has been a translation office in Cuzco 

01:01:56.045 --> 01:01:58.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
since 2004, 

01:01:58.347 --> 01:02:00.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
but as the work grew, 

01:02:00.349 --> 01:02:02.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
so did the need for more office space. 

01:02:02.852 --> 01:02:07.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in 2016, a new RTO was dedicated. 

01:02:07.857 --> 01:02:11.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
The blessings of the translation work 
have been evident. 

01:02:11.928 --> 01:02:16.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
Since the <i>Bible Teach </i>book 
was released in Quechua in 2007, 

01:02:16.566 --> 01:02:18.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
the number of publishers increased 

01:02:18.901 --> 01:02:21.170 line:90% position:50% align:center
from about 700 

01:02:21.170 --> 01:02:25.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
to nearly 1,700 last year. 

01:02:25.208 --> 01:02:27.143 line:90% position:50% align:center
In addition to <i>The Watchtower </i>

01:02:27.143 --> 01:02:29.145 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the <i>Life and Ministry Meeting Workbook, </i>

01:02:29.145 --> 01:02:32.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
videos are translated at this office, 

01:02:32.682 --> 01:02:36.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
ranging from JW Broadcasting 
monthly programs 

01:02:36.753 --> 01:02:40.890 line:90% position:50% align:center
to episodes of <i>Become Jehovah’s Friend.</i>

01:02:40.890 --> 01:02:44.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
There are several regions in Peru 
where Quechua is spoken, 

01:02:44.527 --> 01:02:48.097 line:90% position:50% align:center
all with slightly different dialects 
and expressions. 

01:02:48.097 --> 01:02:51.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hence, 
each translation team 

01:02:51.334 --> 01:02:54.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
has representatives from these areas 

01:02:54.971 --> 01:02:57.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order to ensure that the translation 

01:02:57.106 --> 01:02:59.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
is universally understood 

01:02:59.475 --> 01:03:01.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
among Quechua speakers. 

01:03:01.544 --> 01:03:06.249 line:90% position:50% align:center
Approximately 40 brothers 
and sisters work at the RTO, 

01:03:06.249 --> 01:03:09.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
of which 15 are full-time. 

01:03:09.619 --> 01:03:11.721 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the Cuzco area, 

01:03:11.721 --> 01:03:15.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
there are 28 congregations and 38 groups, 

01:03:15.691 --> 01:03:19.195 line:90% position:50% align:center
